t, with an eye towards results. You will be expected to build, test and optimize a social media strategy with the goal of generating more qualified opportunities for our sales team. In this role you will: Review Braintrust editorial content and pull out various pieces to share on social media. Experiment with different formats (video, images) and messaging to drive engagement. Build and execute the social editorial calendar for our three primary accounts on LinkedIn. (Braintrust account + two Co-Founders\u2019 accounts) Develop a strategy for expanding to other platforms in a low-lift, high impact way. Interact (as Braintrust) with industry leaders, influencers, target audiences, etc. to like/comment/share their content to get more visibility. Report out results; evaluate what\u2019s working leveraging data, and double down on it. Make strategic recommendations to enhance effectiveness. Requirements 3-5 years experience as a Social Media Manager or a similar role internally or at an agency serving B2B companies. Proven to grow social audiences for new company accounts Exhibited interest in the Future of Work, new talent models, and similar narratives/ messaging. Knowledge of LinkedIn, Twitter, Instagram algorithm and for what works and what doesn\u2019t when posting to these platforms. Ability to pull data and formulate a hypothesis about what\u2019s working and what\u2019s not, and make specific recommendations for how to move forward. Proficient in Canva and Hubspot. Experience and comfort working in a fully distributed team environment. Highly creative with an eye for brand building/design. Highly autonomous; self directed and ambitious. Superior communication skills, both written and verbal, in English. Strong attention to detail and organizational skills.\\n This is a remote position. ", 
